elevation /ˌɛlɪˈveɪʃən/

(elevations) 

1. N-COUNT The elevation of a place is its height above sea level. 海拔 

例： We're probably at an elevation of about 13,000 feet above sea level. 我们很可能在海拔13000英尺的高度。 

2. N-COUNT An elevation is a piece of ground that is higher than the area around it. 高地 

例： ...the monument was on an elevation, which could be seen from the church. …这座纪念碑在一块高地上，从教堂能看到。

